      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal concept that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon basic liberties even if it follows proper legal procedures. This doctrine has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe on personal autonomy, such as those related to privacy and marriage. It serves as a vital bulwark against majoritarian tyranny, safeguarding individual freedom against government intrusion.",
